			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2020</a> paper:</span><br><i>Behavior Trees in Action: A Study of Robotics Applications</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/RazanGhzouli.html">Razan Ghzouli</a>, <a href="../profile/ThorstenBerger.html">Thorsten Berger</a>, <a href="../profile/EinarBrochJohnsen.html">Einar Broch Johnsen</a>, <a href="../profile/SwaibDragule.html">Swaib Dragule</a>, <a href="../profile/AndrzejWąsowski.html">Andrzej Wąsowski</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3426425.3426942">10.1145/3426425.3426942</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The paper’s core contribution is tooling/infrastructure for language engineering (e.g., IDE/editor support).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> It reports an empirical evaluation (experiments, study, benchmarks, or measurements).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It emphasizes modularity/composition/integration (embedding or coordinating language components).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6b.html"><span class="tagL">T6B: Industrial</span></a><ul><li> It is motivated by or evaluated in an industrial/practical context.
</li></ul></li></ul>
